article.headline: Hawaii 65, NC A&amp,T 57
article.story: WAILUKU, Hawaii -- Shaquille Stokes scored 19 points and Vander Joaquim added 16 to lead Hawaii to a 65-57 victory against North Carolina A&T on Sunday night. Zane Johnson had 13 points for the Rainbow Warriors (5-4), who hosted a regular-season game on Maui for a second straight year. Marc Hill had 17 points and DaMetrius Upchurch 11 for the Aggies (4-8). Hawaii led 49-48 with 7:45 remaining when two free throws by Stokes ignited a 12-0 run over the next 4:22. Two Joaquim field goals and a three-point play by Stokes highlighted the surge. Joaquim had seven rebounds.
